Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve; ridged inside neck. Clay accreted. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink and pencil 'L635'; ink '48 7.31 341' and '341', deleted. The provenance is clearly Alexandria and the IG entry therefore wrong. Re-registered in error in 1925. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0373.09.
Bibliographic references: IG XII 2 / Inscriptiones Graecae XII 2 (635) (erroneous entry)
